  "prompt": "Will 8 RAC tickets that have changed to CNF, get adjacent berths?",
  "response": "When Reservation Against Cancellation (RAC) tickets get confirmed (CNF) in Indian Railways, the allocation of berths depends on several factors, including availability and the booking system's algorithms. Typically, efforts are made to keep groups together, especially if the tickets were booked under the same PNR (Passenger Name Record).\n\nIf you booked all 8 tickets under the same PNR, there is a higher chance that the system will allocate adjacent or nearby berths to you. However, it is not guaranteed. Factors such as the configuration of the train's coaches and the position of available seats at the time of confirmation play a role in final seating arrangements.\n\nIf you prefer or require specific seating arrangements, you might consider speaking with the ticketing or coach staff at the station or onboard the train who may help you rearrange seat allocations, depending on availability and other passengers' willingness to cooperate.",
